name: Craig Hennecy
text: What a great little gem just 40 minutes from Birmingham.  For family fun or sailing competition, you should check in on this place.  Simply inquire and I promise you will find a welcoming invitation to visit and learn more.

name: Andrew deRussy
text: Great place for sailing, racing, and learning to sail. Membership is not required if you want to learn to sail. Most members race in Thistles, Flying Scots, or J-22s, though you can sail anything here. Wet sand dry slips are available to talk members to store their boats (for a fee). There is even remote control sailboat racing.

name: Gregory Rinehart
text: Friendly, casual atmosphere.  Beautiful location.  Prinarily for sailing families.

name: Eddie R. Hernandez-Gomez
text: Excellent sailing only matched by it's members

name: William Joseph
text: Friendly people.  Great community and fun regattas.
